defaultIn the years 2011-2013 the Histadrut has continued to set as a primary goal the enhancement of 
defaultthe ongoing relationship with PGFT
defaultU. Throughout all these years they 
default have provided legal support for Palestinian workers (in Arabic), encouraged participation in educational and vocational training workshops (particularly in the construction sector where 
defaultthe majority of Palestinians are employed), and distributed brochures printed in Arabic outlining their rights. Most significantly, a new joint Histadrut-PGFTU project for providing legal assistance for Palestinians employed by Israeli employers was set up
default. The project allows Palestinians legally employed by Israeli employers to lodge complaints with the PGFTU who addresses the Histadrut's Legal Department who manages the cases opposite the Israeli employers and if necessary in the Israeli Labour Courts.
defaultT
defaulthroughout 2011-2013 the Histadrut continued to fulfil its financial obligations set out in the 2008 landmark agreement with the PGFTU, according to which half the 
defaulttrade union
default 
defaultfees collected by the Histadrut from legal Palestinian workers employed by Israel
defaulti employers are transferred to the PGFTU. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Histadrut also continues to assist and provide solidarity to the PGFTU in any additional ways it can. For example, in 2011, the Histadrut, upon the request of the PGFTU, assisted the Scottish Fire Brigade's U
defaultnion in transferring humanitarian aid in the form of fire engines, lifesaving firefighting equipment and uniforms to the Nablus fire station.
defaultIn 2013 PGFTU requested the assistance of the Histadrut in finding employment opportunities in the Israeli constr
defaultuction sector for Palestinian workers who are PGFTU members and the Histadrut is currently implementing this venture.
defaultSpecifically in the construction sector where the majority of Palestinians are employed, over the last year the Israeli union has been ho
defaultsting a senior grievance committee which settles all labour disputes between employees and employers. In the framework of the cooperation between the Histadrut and the PGFTU, 
defaultthe Histadrut
default 
defaultrequest
defaults
default 
defaultthe participation of PGFTU representatives in meetings whe
defaultre disputes between Palestinian workers and Israeli employers are discussed.
defaultIn addition, they also allocated in 
defaultthe 
defaultconstruction union headquarters an additional attorney, an Arab citizen, who provides legal consultation specifically for the Palestinian 
defaultemployees. The union also provides vocational training to thousands of Palestinians and migrant workers on the topic of health and safety in working on skyscrapers.
